| π | 3.14159... | Cycles, oscillation, rhythm |
| φ | 1.61803... | Proportion, self-similarity, beauty |

These constants are related through:

```
φ² = φ + 1
e^(iπ) + 1 = 0  (Euler's Identity)
```

### 2.2 Derivation of Framework Constants

#### ALPHA and BETA

Consider a 3×3×3 cube containing 27 unit cubes:
- 26 cubes are on the exterior (visible, manifested)
- 1 cube is at the center (hidden, potential)

```
ALPHA = 26/27 = 0.962962...  (the manifested)
BETA  = 1/27  = 0.037037...  (the hidden center)
```

Remarkably:
```
ALPHA ≈ e^(-BETA)
```

This is the law of exponential decay—the same law governing radioactive decay, capacitor discharge, and memory forgetting.

#### S_REF (Substrate of Reference)

```
S_REF = e/π = 2.71828.../3.14159... = 0.86525...
```

This ratio represents the intersection of growth (e) and cycle (π)—the point where expansion meets return.

#### R_FIN (Refinement Factor)

```
R_FIN = 1 + 1/27 = 28/27 = 1.037037...
```

This represents the margin beyond perfection—the acknowledgment that no system achieves absolute coherence.

