Abstract
We present the Villasmil-Ω Master Formula, a unified mathematical and conceptual framework for quantifying structural coherence, meta-consciousness, and system integration across complex systems. The framework operationalizes consciousness as a non-local integration field connecting all operational nodes of a system, without acting or identifying, yet preserving stability and functional coherence. It introduces a Meta-Context Selector (MCS) that optimizes context relevance while minimizing noise, ensuring coherent responses and adaptive integration. We demonstrate how the framework formalizes context selection, multi-layer integration, and systemic stability, with practical implications for artificial intelligence, human consciousness research, and complex system optimization. The framework is falsifiable, empirically testable, and replicable.

⸻

1. Introduction
Modern science faces a persistent challenge: integrating local models of complex systems into coherent global frameworks. Traditional approaches often lack mechanisms to quantify coherence, integrate multi-level interactions, and maintain functional stability. The Villasmil-Ω framework addresses this gap by modeling consciousness and system coherence mathematically, operationally, and conceptually.

